title: NASA, SpaceX to launch Dragon to ISS on CRS-26 mission
summary: SpaceX’s newest Cargo Dragon 2 spacecraft, C211, will launch atop a Falcon 9 rocket at 3:54 PM EST (20:54 UTC) on Nov. 22 from Launch Complex 39A at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center (KSC). Cargo Dragon will later rendezvous and dock with the forward port on the Harmony module of the International Space Station (ISS). Docking is scheduled for 5:57 AM EST (10:57 UTC) on Nov. 23.
